item.title: Home
item.dc:creator: root
item.content:encoded: Hello there! I'm Don Sijo, a passionate web developer originally from Kerala, India, currently residing in the beautiful land of Canada. It's been an exciting journey since I arrived here five months ago, and I've been captivated by the charm and opportunities this country has to offer. Currently, I'm a student at Georgian College, pursuing a course in Interactive Media Design with a focus on web development. Throughout my time at college, I've delved into various programming languages and web technologies, honing my skills in building captivating and user-friendly websites. One of my proudest achievements is the creation of my personal portfolio website from scratch. With a blend of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, I crafted a showcase of my skills and experiences, demonstrating my proficiency in web development and design. This project reflects my dedication to continuous learning and my commitment to delivering high-quality work. Looking ahead, my goal is to immerse myself in an innovative space as a web developer, where I can contribute my expertise and collaborate with like-minded individuals to create impactful digital experiences.

item.title: About me
item.dc:creator: root
item.content:encoded: Welcome! My name is Don Sijo, and I'm a passionate web developer originally from Kerala, India, currently pursuing my studies at Georgian College in Canada. As I immerse myself in the vibrant field of web development, I find myself constantly inspired by the endless possibilities and creative challenges it presents. My journey into the world of web development began with a spark of curiosity and a desire to explore the digital landscape. At Georgian College, I'm currently enrolled in the Interactive Media Design program, where I'm focusing on honing my skills in web development. Through hands-on projects and coursework, I've delved into various programming languages, including C, C++, C#, Python, and PHP. Additionally, I've developed a strong foundation in front-end development, mastering HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, while also exploring the intricacies of user experience design with tools like Illustrator. One of the highlights of my academic journey has been the creation of my personal portfolio website from scratch. This project allowed me to apply my knowledge and skills in a practical setting, resulting in a platform that showcases my projects, experiences, and capabilities as a web developer. It's a testament to my dedication to continuous learning and my passion for delivering high-quality digital solutions. Looking ahead, I'm excited about the prospect of translating my skills and experiences into meaningful contributions within the web development industry. Whether it's collaborating with like-minded individuals on innovative projects or pushing the boundaries of what's possible in the digital realm, I'm committed to making a positive impact through my work.

item.title: My First Post!
item.dc:creator: root
item.content:encoded:
Hey there, world! 🌟
I'm thrilled to be sharing my very first post on my blog. As a budding web developer, I'm excited to embark on this journey of sharing my thoughts, experiences, and projects with you all.
While this post may be short and sweet, it's the beginning of what I hope will be many more meaningful conversations and collaborations in the future. So stay tuned for more updates, insights, and adventures in the world of web development!
Thanks for joining me on this exciting ride. Here's to new beginnings! 🎉

item.title: Check out my Work for a Diploma Institute
item.dc:creator: root
item.content:encoded: Exciting news! I recently had the opportunity to work on a website project for a diploma institute back in my home country. 🌍 Using my expertise in web development, I collaborated with the institute to design and develop a dynamic website that showcases their programs, faculty, and student achievements. From crafting a user-friendly interface to optimizing the site for search engines, it was a challenging yet rewarding experience. I'm proud of the final result and grateful for the opportunity to contribute to their online presence. If you're curious to see my work in action, check out the website below! https://edusuccess.netlify.app/

item.content:encoded: Hey everyone! I'm excited to share with you my latest project - my personal portfolio website! 🚀 I've poured my heart and soul into crafting this platform from scratch using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. item.title: Refund and Returns Policy
item.dc:creator: root
item.content:encoded:
This is a sample page.

Overview

Our refund and returns policy lasts 30 days. If 30 days have passed since your purchase, we can’t offer you a full refund or exchange.

To be eligible for a return, your item must be unused and in the same condition that you received it. It must also be in the original packaging.

Several types of goods are exempt from being returned. Perishable goods such as food, flowers, newspapers or magazines cannot be returned. We also do not accept products that are intimate or sanitary goods, hazardous materials, or flammable liquids or gases.

Additional non-returnable items:

  • Gift cards
  • Downloadable software products
  • Some health and personal care items

To complete your return, we require a receipt or proof of purchase.

Please do not send your purchase back to the manufacturer.

There are certain situations where only partial refunds are granted:

  • Book with obvious signs of use
  • CD, DVD, VHS tape, software, video game, cassette tape, or vinyl record that has been opened.
  • Any item not in its original condition, is damaged or missing parts for reasons not due to our error.
  • Any item that is returned more than 30 days after delivery

Refunds

Once your return is received and inspected, we will send you an email to notify you that we have received your returned item. We will also notify you of the approval or rejection of your refund.

If you are approved, then your refund will be processed, and a credit will automatically be applied to your credit card or original method of payment, within a certain amount of days.

Late or missing refunds

If you haven’t received a refund yet, first check your bank account again.

Then contact your credit card company, it may take some time before your refund is officially posted.

Next contact your bank. There is often some processing time before a refund is posted.

If you’ve done all of this and you still have not received your refund yet, please contact us at {email address}.

Sale items

Only regular priced items may be refunded. Sale items cannot be refunded.

Exchanges

We only replace items if they are defective or damaged. If you need to exchange it for the same item, send us an email at {email address} and send your item to: {physical address}.

Gifts

If the item was marked as a gift when purchased and shipped directly to you, you’ll receive a gift credit for the value of your return. Once the returned item is received, a gift certificate will be mailed to you.

If the item wasn’t marked as a gift when purchased, or the gift giver had the order shipped to themselves to give to you later, we will send a refund to the gift giver and they will find out about your return.

Shipping returns

To return your product, you should mail your product to: {physical address}.

You will be responsible for paying for your own shipping costs for returning your item. Shipping costs are non-refundable. If you receive a refund, the cost of return shipping will be deducted from your refund.

Depending on where you live, the time it may take for your exchanged product to reach you may vary.

If you are returning more expensive items, you may consider using a trackable shipping service or purchasing shipping insurance. We don’t guarantee that we will receive your returned item.

Need help?

Contact us at {email} for questions related to refunds and returns.
